        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 5:26PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 526 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Sawyerville, or near Greensboro, moving northeast at 30 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Greensboro, Akron, Forkland, Walden Quarters, Moundville Airport,
Eutaw Municipal Airport, Mound State Park, Arcola, Elliots Creek,
Eutaw, Birdine, Harper Hill, Havana, Wedgeworth, Greensboro Municipal
Airport, Moundville, Selden Lock And Dam, Low Gap, Mertz, and Phipps.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 800 PM CDT for
central, southwestern and west central Alabama.</instruction>
